TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_RECENT_VIEWED: The Most Recent Viewed list includes instruments where the instrument details has been viewed.
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_VIEWED_BULLISH: The Most Viewed Bullish list is chosen by counting the number of views of a bullish event for an instrument in the last week.
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_MOST_POPULAR: The Most Popular list is chosen by counting the number of instrument searches over the last 90 days.
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_TRENDING_NOW: The Trending Now list is chosen by counting the number of instrument searches in the last 7 days compared to the last 90 days, normalized as standard deviations.
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_VIEWED_BEARISH: The Most Viewed Bearish list is chosen by counting the number of views of a bearish event for an instrument in the last week.
TRADING_CENTRAL.DESCRIPTION: Based on Trading Central. Trailing Stop ( ”medium” )
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_SENTIMENT_SIGNAL: The Sentiment Signal is based on the market Sentiment Score before trading begins. The sentiment observed at the start of the market session can offer insights into whether the asset is likely to exhibit superior performance, lag behind, or remain steady.
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_SENTIMENT_SCORE: The Sentiment Score indicates how the crowd feels about a financial instrument, ranging from very negative to very positive.
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_SUBJECTIVE: The subjectivity index measures how rational the crowd's opinion of an entity is, which can be helpful in identifying market bubbles. Its score ranges from 0 (very rational) to 100 (very irrational).
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_CONFIDENCE_INDEX: The confidence index is the volume of news evidence backing the sentiment score, indicating how much trust can be placed in it. It is broken down into three levels of low, average, high.
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_SENTIMENT_HISTORY: Shows the variation of the daily sentiment score for the past 90 days.
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_OVERALL_MENTIONS: The number of publications in the past 24 hours that mention the subject, along with a descriptor indicating how it compares to the 7-day average.
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_MENTION_SOURCE: The split represents the distribution of mentions coming from either news websites or media platforms.
TRADING_CENTRAL.TOOLTIP_MOST_DISCUSSED_TOPICS: Display the top 5 trending topics related to the subject over the past 24 hours.
